Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Zest and halve the @lime{½}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1} (stalks and
all). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a garlic press).

Quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}.
Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, sandwich each @british chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of
#baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with
the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 2-3cm thick.

Season the chicken with salt and pepper, then sprinkle both sides evenly with
the @peri peri seasoning{1}. Set aside for now.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the
heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to
pick up some nice colour.

Meanwhile, add the tomatoes, parsley, @olive oil{1}(for the dressing) and a
squeeze of lime juice to a #bowl{}.

Once the corn is charred, add to the bowl and season with salt and pepper. Mix
well, then taste and add more salt, pepper and lime juice if needed.

Put the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, lay in the chicken, turn the heat down to medium and cook until
golden brown, ~{7-8%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat and carefully place the cheese on
top of the chicken. Cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}), then set aside, off the
heat, to allow the cheese to melt, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix the @mayonnaise{32%g}, garlic (add less if
you don't love raw garlic) and lime zest together.

Halve the @glazed burger bun{2}. Pop them onto a baking tray and into the oven
to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the zesty mayo over the bun bases, then top
with the cheesy chicken, a handful of @wild rocket{20} and the bun lids.

Stir the remaining rocket into the charred sweetcorn salad and serve alongside
your chips and burgers. Enjoy!